==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English ''almes'', ''almesse'', from {{L.}} ''eleemosyna''

===Noun===
'''alms'''<!--singular or plural?-->

#Something given to the poor as charity, such as money, clothing or food.
#:''She gave $10 weekly to the poor as alms.''

